<% content_for :title, "Free Rails Bug Capture Tool" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Logister is a free bug capture tool for Ruby on Rails apps. Install the logister-ruby gem and triage issues with grouped errors and request context." %>
<% content_for :canonical_path, root_path %>
<% content_for :og_type, "website" %>
<% content_for :json_ld, json_ld({
  "@context" => "https://schema.org",
  "@type" => "SoftwareApplication",
  "name" => "Logister",
  "applicationCategory" => "DeveloperApplication",
  "operatingSystem" => "Web",
  "description" => "Free bug capture and triage for Ruby on Rails apps via the logister-ruby gem.",
  "url" => "#{request.base_url}#{root_path}",
  "offers" => {
    "@type" => "Offer",
    "price" => "0",
    "priceCurrency" => "USD"
  }
}) %>

<section class="rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm p-6 sm:p-8 mb-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-white to-slate-50/50">
  <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 mb-1">Free for use.<br>Open source and self-hostable.</p>
  <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Catch Rails bugs before your users do.</h1>
  <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 max-w-2xl">
    Logister is a free bug capture tool for Ruby on Rails apps. Install the
    <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-slate-800 text-sm"><a href="https://rubygems.org/gems/logister-ruby" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">logister-ruby</a></code> gem, send errors in minutes, and triage issues
    with grouped stack traces, request context, and occurrence history.
  </p>
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mb-4">
    <%= link_to "Get started free", new_user_registration_path, class: "inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium bg-blue-600 text-white hover:bg-blue-700 no-underline", data: { turbo: false } %>
    <%= link_to "Sign in", new_user_session_path, class: "inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium border border-slate-300 bg-white text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-50 no-underline", data: { turbo: false } %>
  </div>
  <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">
    AI/agent-friendly docs: <a href="/llms.txt" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"><code class="px-1 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100">/llms.txt</code></a>
  </p>
</section>

<section class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-8">
  <article class="rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm p-5">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 mb-2">Step 1</p>
    <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Create a project</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Add your app in Logister and generate an API key.</p>
  </article>
  <article class="rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm p-5">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 mb-2">Step 2</p>
    <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Install the gem</h2>
    <pre class="rounded-lg bg-slate-100 border border-slate-200 p-3 text-sm overflow-x-auto mb-2"><code><a href="https://rubygems.org/gems/logister-ruby" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">gem "logister-ruby"</a></code></pre>
    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Auto-capture unhandled exceptions and send custom events when needed.</p>
  </article>
  <article class="rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm p-5">
    <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 mb-2">Step 3</p>
    <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Fix faster</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Group similar errors, inspect request details, and prioritize by recurrence.</p>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
  <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 mb-3">Why teams use Logister</p>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-slate-600 mb-4">
    <li>Built for Rails workflows and the <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-sm">logister-ruby</code> gem.</li>
    <li>Structured error detail with stacktrace, headers, params, and request IDs.</li>
    <li>Project-level inbox to track unresolved, resolved, ignored, and archived issues.</li>
    <li>Simple setup, no vendor lock-in, and freely available for use.</li>
    <li>Open source repo with self-host docs and Docker support.</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
    <a href="https://github.com/taimoorq/logister" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium border border-slate-300 bg-white text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-50 no-underline">View self-host repo</a>
    <a href="https://github.com/taimoorq/logister-ruby" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium border border-slate-300 bg-white text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-50 no-underline">View gem repo</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
  <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 mb-3">Self-host in minutes</p>
  <pre class="rounded-lg bg-slate-900 text-slate-100 p-4 text-sm overflow-x-auto font-mono mb-3">git clone https://github.com/taimoorq/logister.git
cd logister
cp .env.sample .env
bundle install
bin/rails db:prepare
bin/dev</pre>
  <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Full deployment and production setup steps are documented in the project README.</p>
</section>

<section class="rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
  <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 mb-3">Self-host stack</p>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-slate-600">
    <li>Ruby on Rails + Puma web/API app</li>
    <li>PostgreSQL for users, projects, API keys, and events</li>
    <li>Redis for cache and Sidekiq job processing</li>
    <li>Optional ClickHouse for high-scale analytics queries</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="rounded-xl bg-white border border-slate-200 shadow-sm p-6 mb-6">
  <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 mb-3">What you provide</p>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2 text-slate-600">
    <li>Required: <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-sm">RAILS_MASTER_KEY</code>, <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-sm">DATABASE_URL</code>, <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-sm">REDIS_URL</code>, <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-sm">LOGISTER_ADMIN_EMAILS</code></li>
    <li>Email: <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-sm">LOGISTER_EMAIL_FROM</code> and optionally <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded bg-slate-100 text-sm">SENDGRID_API_KEY</code></li>
    <li>Optional: ClickHouse and Cloudflare Turnstile variables (see README)</li>
  </ul>
</section>
